metadata.name: Lunar Specimen
metadata.description:
These lunar rocks under observation glow iridescently, are indestructible, and appear to move with no external force. Further study is required; however, we predict these specimens may be biological in nature.

They were recently reported as entering the earth's atmosphere and landing across the planet. We've located 450 of them although we believe there are many more. Further reports will be logged and released.
